<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="95.[151,1436,1662,2011]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1662,1687]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Characterized by the following features: wings brown-ochre; forewing in male with complex patterns, apex strongly produced and hook-shaped; antemedial line arched; medial and postmedial lines wavy; oblique line present between postmedial line and apex; discal cell with a black spot; hindwing with slightly wavy medial and postmedial lines and discal cell with a spot; uncus broad and bifid; valva constricted at 
<number box="[1124,1138,1771,1795]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1147,1159,1771,1795]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" value="3.0">3</number>
length, apex narrow and blunt. Female similar to male but larger, paler with weaker pattern, and antenna filiform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
